From 571af3b77723c039ec409449514c3af4ede37101 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 17:34:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] refs: complete helper backend vtable

Implement the remaining ref helper backend callbacks that were
previously stubbed:

  - remove_on_disk: sends "remove" command to helper
  - rename_ref: implemented as read + create + delete via a
    single transaction, matching the files backend approach
  - copy_ref: same as rename but without deleting the source
  - reflog_exists: sends "reflog-exists <refname>" command
  - for_each_reflog_ent: sends "reflog-read <refname>", parses
    entries as "<old-oid> <new-oid> <author> <timestamp> <tz> <msg>"
  - for_each_reflog_ent_reverse: collects all entries from
    "reflog-read" then replays in reverse order
  - delete_reflog: sends "reflog-delete <refname>" command
  - create_reflog: no-op (implicit on first append)
  - reflog_expire: no-op (delegated to helper's own GC)

Add new capability flags to the shared helper process:
  - remove, reflog-read, reflog-append, reflog-exists, reflog-delete

Operations that remain as stubs with justification:
  - reflog_iterator_begin: empty (no protocol command yet)
  - optimize/optimize_required: no-op (helper manages itself)
  - fsck: no-op (integrity checking delegated to helper)
  - ref_iterator_seek: not supported (create new iterator)

Signed-off-by: Aaron Willoughby <aaron@omniband.org>
